title: turtle_head
body:
[b]Turtle Head[/b] is a freeware puzzle-oriented horror game by [i]pikasprey[/i] in 2016 and remade in 2021 by [i]meatpie[/i], made in RPG Maker MV.

h4. Story

Rumors have been making their way around a local high school. Some claim to see figures and hear unusual sounds in the late hours of the night when nobody is expected to be there. This intrigued a small friend group, leading them to sneak into the building and investigate. Alas, they might have found what they were looking for.  

You play as Harriet, a  junior student at the high school. Through her, you will discover the horrific events that unfolded in the local community. The game is intended for players to go into mostly blind, so most of the plot details will have to be discovered on your own.

h4. Characters

title: arcadea
body:
[b]Arcadea[/b] is a freeware puzzle-oriented horror game by [i][[aishin]][/i], made in RPG Maker VX Ace.

h4. Story

In the world of Arcadea, people can accomplish their dreams. How? Through video games of course! Everybody who lives in Arcadea has a special arcade machine they can visit in their dreams that lets them fulfill their strongest wishes. Whether it’s to go on an adventure, or make friends, or fall in love, or solve a mystery, or completely start a new life, there’s a game made just for them...By playing these arcade machines, you can find out a lot about a person…their aspirations and their goals for example. Oh and also their regrets, their insecurities, and their biggest mistakes. Huh...video games can’t be that deep right? Must be a bug or something....Speaking of which, how do you even get to this world in the first place? 

The game follows Maisie, a new arrival to Arcadea. She’s not very interested in all this gaming stuff; her only goal is to find an important person. But along the way, she can’t help but be roped into other people’s problems. She also can’t help that the arcade machines seem to glitch around her. Alot.

title: airpot
body:
A portable vacuum insulated hot beverage dispenser with a glass or stainless steel liner inside. Airpots can be filled with hot beverages such as [[tea]] and [[coffee]] and are used to keep beverages warm for several hours. Since airpots do not require electricity, they are easy to use outdoors or in temporary locations such as conference rooms and formal receptions.

It resembles a portable version of a [[water boiler]], though it doesn't have the heating function it does.

title: hellsing
body:
A 1997-2009 seinen manga written and illustrated by [[Hirano Kouta]], originally serialized in [i]Young King OURs[/i] for 89 chapters, which were collected in ten volumes. It was adapted into a 13-episode television anime (2001-2002) and a 10-episode OVA series (2006-2012), as well as a spin-off called [[Hellsing: The Dawn]].

Set in the [[United Kingdom]] during modern era. The story is centered around the Royal Order of Protestant Knights, also known by the series' titular name as "Hellsing Organization", which is responsible for eliminating supernatural threats that would threaten the country. Particularly [[vampire]]s. The Hellsings is led by [[Integra Hellsing]], the descendant of vampire hunter Abraham von Helsing, as well as her right hand man and the most capable vampire hunter, [[Alucard (Hellsing)|]] - himself the [[dracula|original and the very first vampire]] who swore loyalty to the Hellsing family after his defeat to Abraham Helsing.

title: vigneron_submachine_gun
body:
The [b]Vigneron[/b] is a 9mm Parabellum [[submachine gun]] manufactured in Belgium during the 1950s, designed by a retired Belgian army Colonel, Georges Vigneron. It was intended to replace the [[Sten gun|Sten]]. It features few elements from previous SMG designs, such as tubular upper receiver and sliding wire buttstock that resembles [[m3 submachine gun|M3 Grease Gun]] one. The [[gun]] is relatively accurate on semi-auto mode due to its barrel length.

This tag applies to all variants, the original Vigneron M1 and the improved M2.

title: arisaka
body:
The [b]Arisaka[/b] family of [[bolt action]] rifles were a series of Japanese weapons designed by Colonel Nariakira Arisaka. They were the standard weapons of the Japanese Empire from 1898 to 1945 and were used in [[World War I]] and [[World War II]]. 

The Arisaka rifles were derived in part from the German Mauser, especially the 5-round internal magazine fed by a stripper clip. The most common versions were the 6.5x50mm Type 38 long rifle and 7.7x58mm Type 99 short rifle. Less common but notable variants are the folding-bayonet Type 44 carbine and Type 97 sniper rifle (both derived from the Type 38), and the Type 2 paratrooper rifle (based on the Type 99). 

Arisaka rifles were marked with [[kikumon|the Imperial Seal of Japan]] (a Chrysanthemum), designating them as the property of the Emperor.

title: void_termina
body:
A dark, godlike creature appearing in [i][[Kirby: Star Allies]][/i] as the true antagonist and final boss.

He is worshipped by [[Hyness]] [[francisca_(kirby)|and]] [[flamberge_(kirby)|his]] [[zan_partizanne|underlings]] for reasons unknown beyond some kind of omnicidal revenge plot against an ancient civilization.

Ancient texts suggest that he only knows destruction and will carry it out with his mere existence. He is also apparently able to reincarnate from positive or negative energy. This information along with various patterns and designs shared by previous [i]Kirby[/i] villains suggests a heavy connection to [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], [[Zero (kirby)|]] (and [[Zero Two (kirby)|]] by extension), the [[Master Crown]], and even [[Kirby]] himself.

However, since he is implied to be able to reincarnate with positive energy, it is possible for him to reawaken as a friend and provide protection and joy to the universe rather than its destructive end.

[spoiler]His true form has two alternative forms fought in [i]Star Allies'[/i] boss rush mode: [[Void Soul]] and [[Void (kirby)|]][/spoiler]

title: dark_mind
body:
The true antagonist and final boss of [i][[Kirby and the Amazing Mirror]][/i]. He shows himself after [[Kirby]] defeats [[Dark Meta Knight]] a second time. With help from [[Meta Knight]] and [[Shadow Kirby]], Kirby is able to defeat the dark tyrant with ease.

His resemblence to [[nightmare_(Kirby)|Nightmare]] and [[zero_(kirby)|Zero]] suggests that he may be a counterpart to Nightmare, [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], or both. [spoiler][[void (kirby)|Void's]] ability to mimic him supports this theory.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]He is implied to have survived his defeat at Kirby's hands and may have been responsible for [[Queen Sectonia]]'s corruption and the appearance of King D. Mind.[/spoiler]

body:

Ever since the game's true ending, she has also been shown to be a possible love interest of Kirby's.

She is also one of the few humanoid Kirby characters, and is one of the few Kirby characters to have a human-like face.

She also appears in [i][[Kirby: Star Allies]][/i] as a Dream Friend with [[Adeleine]] by her side. She is part of the second wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[Daroach]] and [[Dark Meta Knight]].

title: gooey_(kirby)
body:
A mysterious, goofy blob that first appears in [i][[kirby's_dream_land_2|Kirby's Dream Land 2]][/i]. He would replenish [[Kirby|Kirby's]] health upon being freed from the clutches of a mid-boss.

He later appears in [i][[kirby's_dream_land_3|Kirby's Dream Land 3]][/i], where he acts as Kirby's Player 2 companion during the adventure. 

He is a small blue blob with bulbous eyes, and can attack with his long [[tongue]], not unlike [[Yoshi]]. At some point in [i]Dream Land 3[/i], he is also seen with the same kind of orange petals/orbs as [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], further supporting the fact that he is a part of it that had turned good.

He makes a return in [i][[kirby:_star_allies|Kirby Star Allies]][/i] as a Dream Friend. He was part of the first wave of post-launch Dream Friends alongside [[rick_(kirby)|Rick]], [[kine_(kirby)|Kine]], [[coo_(kirby)|Coo]], and [[marx (kirby)|Marx]].

title: dark_nebula

When [[Daroach]] stole the chest upon Kirby defeating Meta Knight, Dark Nebula immediately possessed the Squeak Squad leader and proceeded to carry out its evil plans. As expected, Kirby corrected his childish mistake by promptly laying the smackdown on the dark lord and saving the day once more.

Through the working of Causality, it finds its way to the hand of a person who eventually reaches his or her lowest point of despair, upon which the Behelit activates by forming the grotesque blood-crying face above and screaming. This summons the God Hand for a special ceremony that usually ends with the bearer sacrificing someone dear to them in order to become an Apostle.

title: hibiki_(kancolle)
body:
Hibiki is 22nd Fubuki-class destroyer and/or 2nd Akatsuki-class destroyer in [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i].
Character design by [[Yadokari (migihashi)|]], voiced by [[Suzaki Aya]].

h4. Appearance and personality
The Akatsuki-class wears a white and dark blue [[serafuku]] with a "III" somewhere on themselves as well as some form of black legwear.

Hibiki herself has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair|white]], [[light_blue_hair|light blue]], [[aqua_hair|aqua]], or [[grey hair]], [[blue eyes|blue]] or [[grey eyes]], she wears [[black thighhighs]] and a [[flat cap]]. The "III" is on her hat.

A stoic girl and a russophile, she sometimes uses appropriate (if rudimentary) Russian in her dialogue. Her catchphrase is "хорошо" or "[[horosho]]". She is one of four girls with a remodeling which changes her name. In this case, her second remodeling turns her into her post-war self: [[Verniy (kancolle)|Verniy]]. She also has the nickname of "Phoenix" due to her surviving from heavy damage several times during the war, avoiding more difficult battles in the process as well.

h4. History
The historical destroyer Hibiki was handed over to the USSR in 1947 as a war prize. She continued to serve the Soviet Navy until 1953 when she was transferred to the reserve fleet. She remained there until 1970 when she finally sunk as a practice target. Her wreck was "discovered in 2012":http://safety-stop.ru/hibiki/ near Karamzin Islands, Vladivostok and is now a popular wreck diving site.

title: raiden_(metal_gear)
body:
One of the main characters of the [[metal_gear_(series)|Metal Gear]] franchise. He was a child soldier in the Liberian Civil War; when [[Solidus Snake]] made him his adopted son. He was known by nicknames of Jack The Ripper and White Devil, due to his remarkably outstanding kill record in the conflict. He was the hero of the Big Shell Incident, and assisted [[Solid Snake]] during The Guns of the Patriots. 

In [[Metal Gear Rising: Revengeance]], Raiden was transformed into a [[cyborg]] after numerous fights have crippled his human body and become a mercenary. The game revolves around his one-man war against World Marshal, a PMC backed by Senator [[Steven Armstrong]], and his ideological conflict.

After his resurgence of popularity, he is often paired with [[Nier:Automata]]'s [[2B_(nier:automata)|]] due to both [[trait connection|having several similar traits]], primarily being a [[white hair]]ed characters who has their body enhanced by cybernetics, and using sword as a weapon of choice.

He is voiced by Quinton Flynn in North America, and by Horiuchi Kenyuu [堀内 賢雄] in Japan.

body:
[b]Private First Class Robert "Lucky Peaches" Hugh Leckie[/b] (December 18, 1920 – December 24, 2001) was a [[united_states_marine_corps|United States Marine]] and an author of books about the [[military]] history of the [[United States]], Catholic history and culture, sports books, fiction books, autobiographies, and children's books. As a young man, he served with the 1st Marine Division during [[World War II]]; his service as a machine gunner and a scout during the war greatly influenced his work.

Leckie's war memoir, [i]Helmet for My Pillow[/i], along with [[eugene_bondurant_sledge|Eugene B. Sledge]]'s book [i]With the Old Breed[/i], formed the basis for the HBO series [[The Pacific]] (2010), the follow-up series to [[Band of Brothers]] (2001). [b]The Guadalcanal Campaign[/b], also known as [b]The Battle of Guadalcanal[/b] and codenamed [b]Operation Watchtower[/b] by [[united_states|American]] forces, was a [[military]] campaign fought between 7 August 1942 and 9 February 1943 on and around the island of [[guadalcanal_(island)|Guadalcanal]] in the Pacific theater of [[World War II]]. 

It was the first major land offensive by Allied forces against the Empire of [[Japan]]. It ended in a major Allied [[victory]] that caused the complete Japanese withdrawal from the island and the beginning of Allied offensive operations in the Pacific Ocean.

title: battle_of_peleliu
body:
[b]The Battle of Peleliu[/b], codenamed [b]Operation Stalemate II[/b] by the US [[military]], was fought between the [[United States]] and [[Japan]] during the Mariana and Palau Islands campaign of [[World War II]], from 15 September to 27 November 1944, on the [[island]] of Peleliu.

US Marines of the 1st Marine Division and then soldiers of the US Army's 81st Infantry Division fought to capture an airfield on the small coral island of Peleliu. The battle was part of a larger offensive campaign known as [b]Operation Forager[/b], which ran from June to November 1944 in the Pacific Theater.

It ended in a very costly American [[victory]].

The battle is extensively featured in the American historical [[war]] drama series, [[The Pacific]].

title: zechs_merquise
body:
Character from [[Gundam Wing]]. Zechs is a pilot for OZ, and is renowned for his great skills, earning him the moniker of "Lightning Baron". He is mostly associated with the [[Tallgeese]], a [[mobile suit]] he chose to unearth and pilot despite knowing its performance could kill him (he even notoriously suffered a heart attack when he piloted it for the first time despite him being a very healthy young man), and the [[Gundam Epyon]], his traditional red mobile suit as the "[[Char Aznable|Char]] Clone" of the series.

His usual attire is pretty much almost identical to [[Mobile Suit Gundam]]'s [[Char Aznable]], with minor changes such as his longer hair, different mask design and lack of Zeon elements in his outfit. Nevertheless, he is almost universally regarded as the one that most resembles Char out of all the "Char Clones" - sometimes above [[Full Frontal]], who is an actual clone of Char.

[spoiler]His birth name is actually [[Milliardo Peacecraft]] - meaning he is indeed the older brother of [[Relena Peacecraft]].[/spoiler]

title: 1980_iranian_embassy_siege
body:
A [b][[historical event]][/b] that took place from 30 April to 5 May [[1980]], after a group of six [[gun|armed]] men stormed the [[Iran]]ian embassy on Prince's Gate in South Kensington, [[London]]. The [[terrorist|gunmen]] were [[Iran]]ian Arab [[terrorist]]s campaigning for sovereignty of Khuzestan Province. They took 26 [[hostage]]s, including embassy staff, several visitors, and a [[police]] officer. 

By the sixth day, the gunmen proceed to [[murder|kill]] a hostage and [[throwing|threw]] his [[corpse|body]] out of the embassy on the evening. The [[Special Air Service]] (SAS) initiated "Operation Nimrod" to rescue the hostages, abseiling from the roof and forcing entry through the [[window]]s. During the 17-minute raid they rescued all but one of the remaining hostages and killed five of the six hostage-takers. The sole remaining gunman served 27 years in [[prison]].

The SAS raid became the subject of multiple documentaries and works of fiction, including several films and TV series.

title: kanne_(sousou_no_frieren)
body:
Third-class mage who participated in the first-class mage examinations, where she was paired with [[Frieren]] and her childhood friend [[Lawine (sousou_no_frieren)|]] for the first exam.

Kanne is a young, [[petite]] girl of similar stature to Frieren. She has [[orange eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[orange hair]], which is styled into uneven bangs and two [[pigtails]] with strands that reach the bottom of her face. When she lets down her hair, it gets slightly wavy and reaches the edge of her face.

Her usual outfit is composed of a [[cropped shirt|cropped]] [[white shirt|white top]] with [[puffy sleeves]] that reach her elbows and dark [[green shorts]] with a [[white belt]]. The top is decorated with dark green edges and has shoulders cutouts and triangle-shaped cutouts near her chest and on her back. She additionally wears [[white footwear|white]] [[knee boots|over-the-knee boots]] and white [[bracelet|bracelets]].

When performing spells as a mage, Kanne uses a long, straight [[mage staff|staff]] with a jeweled center and three prongs that are reminiscent of crystals.

title: aisin-gioro_puyi
body:
The last [[Chinese Empire|Emperor of China]], and final monarch of the [[Qing dynasty]]. Would later be declared Emperor of the Imperial Japanese puppet state of [[Manchukuo]]. Following the end of World War 2, he would remain imprisoned until 1959, when he had been released after "successful reeducation" and "Communist remodeling", with endorsement from the [[china|CCP]]. He was frequently targeted by the youth [[Red Guard]]s during the [[Cultural Revolution]], resulting in his health declining and dying in 1967.

Has seen renewed interest on [[TikTok]] as a result of Puyi impersonator "4lvi3yjy0":[https://www.tiktok.com/@4lvi3yjy0], dancing around China as Puyi, to the tune of Harry Styles' [i]As It Was[/i].

body:
[b]Elizabeth Alexandra Mary[/b] of the House of Windsor (21 April 1926 - 8 September 2022)

In September 2015 she became the longest reigning monarch of the United Kingdom and since October 2016, was the world's longest-reigning monarch. Elizabeth passed away peacefully on 8th September 2022 at the age of 96.
Her successor is Charles Windsor, her eldest son, who took on the royal name "[[Charles III]]".

title: sig_sg550
body:
The [b]SIG SG550[/B] 5.56×45mm NATO [[assault rifle]] designed and manufactured by [[SIG SAUER|Swiss Arms AG]] (former division of SIG Holding AG), adopted into service in 1990. It features a reciprocating charging handle, a [[folding stock]], an ambidextrous safety, closed bolt gas-actuated long-stroke piston mechanism and manually adjustable gas valve which make the [[rifle]] very reliable.

This tag can also apply to the slightly shorter SG551 variant, and the discontinued semi-auto only SG550-1 for [[sniper rifle|designated marksman]] role (with [[scope]] and [[bipod]]).

title: croupier
body:
A croupier or dealer is someone appointed at a gambling table to assist in the conduct of the game, especially in the distribution of bets and payouts. Croupiers are typically employed by casinos.

Originally a 'croupier' meant one who stood behind a gambler, with extra reserves of cash to back him up during a gambling session. The word derived from 'croup' (the rump of a horse) and was by way of analogy to one who rode behind on horseback. It later came to refer to one who was employed to collect the money from a gaming-table.

A female croupier's uniform usually consists of a shirt and tie with a [[vest]], and a [[miniskirt]] or slacks.

title: armd
body:
A fictional [[spacecraft]] from the [[MACROSS]] science fiction series.

The [b]ARMD Class Space Carrier[/b] (ARMD being an acronym for [b]A[/b]rmaments [b]R[/b]igged-up [b]M[/b]oving [b]D[/b]eck) is a human built warship designed as [[space]] carrier for [[variable fighter]]s and other [[U.N. Spacy]] [[mecha]].

Built by OTEC Company, the ARMD carriers featured OverTechnology with gravity control systems, a reaction heat pile system and even a fold drive (though this hyperspace navigation system was never implemented in actual combat). At 0.4 km in length, the ARMD carriers were much smaller than the large [[SDF-1]] "Macross" and both ARMD-01 and ARMD-02 were originally meant to dock with the larger craft when the ship achieved orbit during its maiden voyage.

As a carrier vessel, the ARMDs held numerous ships and mecha. ARMD-01 held 78 SF-A3 Lancer II space fighters and 270 [[QF-3000E]] [[Ghost drone]] fighters (as well as an unknown number of [[VF-1]] variable fighters) just prior to [[Choujikuu Yousai Macross|Space War I]] (the events of [i]Super Dimension Fortress Macross[/i]). 

In addition to several hundred fighters, the ARMD carrier was armed with many weapons including beam cannons, small anti-aircraft cannons and [[missile]] launchers as well as several anti-ship medium sized and large missiles with multiple [[nuclear weapon|reaction warheads]]. 

The ARMD possessed many large [[vernier thrusters]] nozzles positioned all over the craft. These powerful [[thrusters]] granted the ARMD excellent maneuverability in space and also proved very useful for combat engagement and evasion.

In [[real life]] this ship was designed by [[Miyatake Kazutaka]] in the early [[1980s_(style)|80s]] for the first Macross TV series. The ship was renamed the [b]Armor Class Space Carrier[/b] in the [[Robotech]] adaptation from 1985.

h4. See also

title: battletech
body:
[i][b]BattleTech[/b][/i] is a long-running American wargaming [[military]] [[science fiction]] and [[mecha]] franchise launched by FASA Corporation in 1984, acquired by WizKids in 2000, and owned since 2003 by "Topps":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topps company.

The game was heavily influenced by real [[robot]] anime like [[Gundam]] and [[Macross]]. It is set predominantly in the 31st Century, where humanity has colonized numerous star systems, but is divided among a number of feudal "Great Houses" and various minor states after its ruling government, the Star League, collapsed several centuries prior. War is a frequent occurrence and is often waged with BattleMechs at the forefront, giant robots that are treated more akin to walking tanks than the ultimate weapon. 

The series began with FASA's debut of the mid-80s [[board game]] [i]BattleTech[/i] (originally named [i]BattleDroids[/i]) by Jordan Weisman and L. Ross Babcock III. 

It has since grown to include numerous expansions to the original game, several computer and home [[game_console|console]] [[video game]]s, a collectible card game, a series of more than 100 novels, an animated television series and more.

While Battletech initially used licensed designs from [i][[Taiyou no Kiba Dougram]][/i] and [i][[Choujikuu Yousai Macross]][/i], these were later replaced with original designs.

Relatively well-known titles in Japan are:

* Tabletop role-playing game (Japanese: メックウォリアーRPG; sometimes called メックウォリアーTRPG)
* [b][i]MechWarrior[/i][/b] (1989 video game) (Super Famicom: バトルテック / PC-98 & X68000: バトルテック ~奪われた聖杯~ released in 1992 in Japan simply as [b][i]Battletech[/i][/b])

A fictional, massive [[alien]] [[spacecraft]] from the [[MACROSS]] [[science fiction]] series.

The [b]Quiltra-Queleual Class Landing Ship Tank[/b] like nearly all [[Zentradi]] ships of the line, has been in active service for hundreds of millennia. 

Another product of the war machines used during the ancient Schism War of the old [[Protoculture]] Stellar Republic, the Quiltra-Queleual serves the role of a planetary assault ship. More than any of the other Zentradi capital ships, this vessel devotes the vast majority of internal volume to [[mecha]] bays and hangars for [[Regult]] battle pods, [[Gnerl]] fighters and re-entry craft. 

This ship features several launching hatches for efficient deployment including a large re-entry pod [[hatch]] in its bow. While not specifically designed for ship-to-ship combat, the Quiltra-Queleual still features a moderate number of anti-ship and anti-fighter [[energy cannon]]s and [[missile]] weapons for attack and defense.

title: dunkirk_evacuation
body:
[b]The Dunkirk Evacuation[/b], codenamed [b]Operation Dynamo[/b] and also known as [b]The Miracle of Dunkirk[/b], or simply [b]Dunkirk[/b], was the evacuation of more than 338,000 Allied soldiers during the early part of [[World War II]] from the beaches and harbour of Dunkirk, in the north of [[France]], between 26 May and 4 June 1940. 

The operation commenced after large numbers of Belgian, [[united_kingdom|British]], and French troops were cut off and surrounded by [[germany|German]] troops during the six-week [[Battle of France]]. In a speech to the House of Commons, British Prime Minister [[Winston Churchill]] called this "a colossal military disaster", saying "the whole root and core and brain of the British Army" had been stranded at Dunkirk and seemed about to be destroyed or captured. 

In his "We shall fight on the beaches":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/We_shall_fight_on_the_beaches speech on 4 June, after the operation had successfully ended, he hailed their rescue as [i]"a miracle of deliverance...".[/i]

title: queadluun-rau

[[Zentradi]] one-man tactical aerospace [[alien]] [[power armor]] that first appeared in [[Choujikuu Yousai Macross]] science fiction anime TV series from 1982.

The [[Quimeliquola]] [b]Queadluun-Rau[/b], also known as the [b]Q-Rau[/b], is one of the most advanced and dangerous Zentradi [[mecha]]. It is very fast, heavy armored and highly maneuverable thanks to its inertia vector control system, several [[vernier thrusters]] and advanced thermonuclear reactor. 

This power armor is armed with two mid-range energy cannons on its torso, two triple-barreled rapid fire energy [[arm cannon]]s on its forearms, two micro-missile launchers on its back and two on its legs with dozens of missiles each. Because of its characteristics and weaponry, this mecha is used mostly in enemy fighter interception and long range aggressive-reconaissance roles, rather than anti-capital ship combat. 

The Q-Rau is the mecha of choice for Zentradi [[starfighter]] aces such as [[Millia Jenius]].

In the original 1982 Macross TV series the mecha was used by the female fleets of the Zentradi armada, while in the 1984 film adaptation of the series, [[Macross: Do You Remember Love?]] the Q-Rau was used by the [[Meltrandi]] fleet (enemies of the Zentradi fleet) only.   

In [[real life]] the Queadluun-Rau was designed by [[Miyatake Kazutaka]] in the early 80s.

title: shin_(hokuto_no_ken)
body:
[b]Shin[/b] ([b]シン[/b])  is [[Kenshiro]]'s first major adversary in [[Hokuto no Ken]] series. Shin represents the Star of Martyrdom (殉星, Junsei) and is the successor of the Nanto Koshu Ken (南斗孤鷲拳, "South Star Lone Eagle Fist") style.

Shin was initially Kenshiro's friend and rival, who secretly desired Kenshiro's fiance [[Yuria (Hokuto no Ken)|]] from afar, but knew Yuria's heart was for Kenshiro and gave up to pursue her. After some motivation [spoiler]from [[Jagi]][/spoiler], Shin challenged Kenshiro, after destroying Ryuken's grave stone, and defeated him, engraving the seven scars on his chest afterwards; subsequently taking off with Yuria by force.

After his first fight with Kenshiro, Shin formed the "King's Army" consists of outlaws ranging from Nanto Seiken users to brutish thugs. His army conquered a city that Shin later named it "Southern Cross", where he ruled as an oppressive tyrant who often committed various atrocities in the name of Yuria, much to her distraught and frustration. 

h4. Known moves

* 南斗獄屠拳 ([i][[Nanto Gokuto Ken]][/i])
** A flying kick which temporarily disables the enemy by cutting the joints in their arms and legs. Known for its iconic pose of having one leg folded in, one leg pointed out and arms extended while in the air.

* 南斗千首龍撃 ([i]Nanto Senshu Ryugeki[/i])
** A series of rapid hand stabbing techniques.

* 南斗飛竜拳 ([i]Nanto Hiryu Ken[/i])
** A series of rapid fist strikes. The result of the attack makes his enemy crack all over like rock before Shin deals a finishing blow.

title: chokha
body:
A type of overcoat that is part of the traditional clothing of people from the Caucasus, such as Georgians, Circassians, and Chechens, among others, as well as other groups that have interacted with them, like Russian Cossacks.

They are most recognizable from the attached [[gazyr|gazyrs]] - several fabric tubes lined up side-by-side in a row on the breast, formerly used to hold rifle charges, but now mainly decorative. Chokhas also characteristically have a v-shaped or triangular neckline that is often very deep, in many cases extending down to the breasts, exposing the wearer's shirt (usually [[dress shirt|button-up]]) underneath. The bottom hem of a chokha is generally pleated and extends down far enough to cover the knees, but not touch the ground. They may be any color, but are prototypically black or some other dark color.
